box model
---------
+ it is a container which conists of content, padding, border and margin.
+ every web pages consists of box-model.
+ the HTML file consist of HTMl elements. bydefault the content of element will display in the top-left corner of the document.


padding
--------
it is a space around the HTML content.
it has 4 properties

- padding-top: px; --> it adds space top of the content. 
- padding-right: px; --> it adds space right of the content. 
- padding-bottom: px; --> it adds space bottom of the content. 
- padding-left: px; --> it adds space left of the content.

shorthand property:-
        padding: px; --> applies all sides.
        padding: px px; --> first value top and bottom second value left and right.
        padding: px px px ; --> first value top, second value left and right third value bottom.
        padding: px px px px ; --> 1st - top, 2nd - right, 3rd - bottom, 4th - left.


border
---------
it is the region between the padding and margin or it is the space around the padding.

- border-width: px; --> width of the border.
- border-style: solid, dotted, double, dashed, inset, outset, grooved; --> these are the border styles we can apply.
- border-color: ; --> here we can pass any color as an argument

shorthand property:-
        border: width style color;



margin
---------
it is space around the border.
it has 4 properties.

- margin-top: px; --> it adds space top of the content. 
- margin-right: px; --> it adds space right of the content. 
- margin-bottom: px; --> it adds space bottom of the content. 
- margin-left: px; --> it adds space left of the content.

shorthand property:-
        margin: px; --> applies all sides.
        margin: px px; --> first value top and bottom second value left and right.
        margin: px px px ; --> first value top, second value left and right third value bottom.
        margin: px px px px ; --> 1st - top, 2nd - right, 3rd - bottom, 4th - left.



how to calculate the height and width of HTML elements

- formula to calculate width
        content-width + padding-left + padding-right + border-left + border-right + margin-left + margin-right.

- formula to calculate height
        content-height + padding-top + padding-bottom + border-top + border-bottom + margin-top + margin-bottom.

example:- 
        p{
            height: 100px;
            width: 200px;
            border: 5px solid red;
            margin: 10px 20px;
            padding: 2px 4px 8px;
        }

        height:- 100+2+8+5+5+10+10 = 140px
        width:- 200+4+4+5+5+20+20 = 258px
